b'' b'note the followup-to: header b'' b'is there a collection of forms routines that can be used with curses?' b'if so where is it located?' b'' b"on my svr4 amiga unix box, i've got -lform, -lmenu, and -lpanel for" b'use with the curses library. guess what they provide? b'' b"unix press, ie. prentice-hall, has a programmer's guide for these" b'tools, referred to as the fmli (forms mgmt language interface) and' b"eti (extended terminal interface), now in it's 2nd edition. it is" b'isbn b'' b'paraphrased from the outside back cover:' b'' b'fmli is a high-level programming tool for creating menus, forms,' b'and text frames. eti is a set of screen management library' b'subroutines that promote fast development of application programs' b'for window, panel, menu, and form manipulation.' b'' b'the fmli is a shell package which reads ascii text files and produces' b'screen displays for data entry and presentation. it consists of a' b'"shell-like" environment of the "fmli" program and it\'s database' b'files. it is section 1f in the unix press manual.' b'' b'the eti are subroutines, part of the 3x manual section, provide' b'support for a multi-window capability on an ordinary ascii terminal' b'with controls built on top of the curses library.' b'' b'thanks' b'-mark steele' b'' b'--' b'frank "crash" edwards edwards edwards consulting' b"data: don't ask uunet to route it it's sloooow." b'there will be times in life when everyone you meet smiles and pats you on' b'the back and tells you how great you are so hold on to your wallet.' 